</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="44C472C3864CC35E2D29A22318C7F80B" pageId="6" pageNumber="463" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="0C612148864CC35E2D29A22318C7F80B" blockId="6.[1362,2570,1222,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="3EAAFD5A864CC35E2D29A22316F3F876" bold="true" box="[1364,1709,1895,1924]" pageId="6" pageNumber="463">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. The Lake Baptista Titi occurs in a relatively small area, which is nevertheless buffered from most anthropogenic impacts at the present time. A small part ofits distribution is in the Andira-Marau Indigenous Reservation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
